#!/bin/sh
# ProtOS ISO Init — minimal initramfs that mounts squashfs from ISO
# This script runs from the tiny initramfs, finds the ISO,
# mounts the squashfs rootfs with an overlayfs writable layer,
# then switch_root into the real system.

# Mount essential virtual filesystems
mount -t proc none /proc
mount -t sysfs none /sys
mount -t devtmpfs none /dev
mount -t tmpfs none /tmp

echo "ProtOS: Mounting root filesystem from ISO..."

# Wait for block devices to appear
sleep 1
mdev -s 2>/dev/null || true

# Try to find and mount the ISO/disk containing our squashfs
# For CD-ROM: /dev/sr0
# For virtio disk (UTM/QEMU): /dev/vda, /dev/vdb
# For USB: /dev/sda, /dev/sdb
# For NVMe: /dev/nvme0n1
mkdir -p /mnt/iso /mnt/squash /mnt/tmpfs /mnt/root

ISO_FOUND=0
for dev in /dev/sr0 /dev/vda /dev/vdb /dev/sda /dev/sdb /dev/nvme0n1; do
    [ -b "$dev" ] || continue
    if mount -t iso9660 -o ro "$dev" /mnt/iso 2>/dev/null; then
        if [ -f /mnt/iso/boot/protos/rootfs.squashfs ]; then
            ISO_FOUND=1
            break
        fi
        umount /mnt/iso
    fi
    # Also try without specifying fs type (for raw disk images)
    if mount -o ro "$dev" /mnt/iso 2>/dev/null; then
        if [ -f /mnt/iso/boot/protos/rootfs.squashfs ]; then
            ISO_FOUND=1
            break
        fi
        umount /mnt/iso
    fi
done

# Also try partition devices if whole-disk didn't work
if [ "$ISO_FOUND" = "0" ]; then
    for dev in /dev/vda1 /dev/sda1 /dev/nvme0n1p1; do
        [ -b "$dev" ] || continue
        if mount -o ro "$dev" /mnt/iso 2>/dev/null; then
            if [ -f /mnt/iso/boot/protos/rootfs.squashfs ]; then
                ISO_FOUND=1
                break
            fi
            umount /mnt/iso
        fi
    done
fi

if [ "$ISO_FOUND" = "0" ]; then
    echo "ERROR: Could not find ProtOS rootfs.squashfs on any device!"
    echo "Available block devices:"
    ls /dev/sd* /dev/vd* /dev/sr* /dev/nvme* 2>/dev/null
    echo ""
    echo "Dropping to emergency shell..."
    exec /bin/sh
fi

echo "ProtOS: Found rootfs on $dev"

# Mount the squashfs (read-only)
if ! mount -t squashfs -o ro /mnt/iso/boot/protos/rootfs.squashfs /mnt/squash; then
    echo "ERROR: Failed to mount rootfs.squashfs!"
    echo "Dropping to emergency shell..."
    exec /bin/sh
fi

echo "ProtOS: Squashfs mounted, setting up overlay..."

# Create writable overlay using tmpfs
mount -t tmpfs -o size=50% tmpfs /mnt/tmpfs
mkdir -p /mnt/tmpfs/upper /mnt/tmpfs/work

# Mount overlayfs: squashfs (lower/ro) + tmpfs (upper/rw)
if mount -t overlay overlay -o lowerdir=/mnt/squash,upperdir=/mnt/tmpfs/upper,workdir=/mnt/tmpfs/work /mnt/root; then
    echo "ProtOS: Overlay filesystem ready"
else
    # Fallback: if overlayfs fails, just use squashfs read-only
    echo "WARN: OverlayFS failed, using read-only squashfs"
    umount /mnt/root 2>/dev/null
    mount --move /mnt/squash /mnt/root
fi

# Move virtual filesystems into new root
mkdir -p /mnt/root/proc /mnt/root/sys /mnt/root/dev /mnt/root/tmp /mnt/root/run
mount --move /proc /mnt/root/proc
mount --move /sys /mnt/root/sys
mount --move /dev /mnt/root/dev
mount --move /tmp /mnt/root/tmp

# Create mount points for ISO and squashfs inside new root
# (so they stay mounted and accessible for the installer)
mkdir -p /mnt/root/mnt/iso /mnt/root/mnt/squash
mount --move /mnt/iso /mnt/root/mnt/iso 2>/dev/null || true

echo "ProtOS: Switching root..."

# Switch to the real root filesystem
exec switch_root /mnt/root /sbin/init
